  "body": "GunmanвҖҷs Motive Probed After DC Gala Attack\nBloomberg Morning Briefing Americas вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ \nвҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ \nвҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ \nвҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ \nвҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ \nвҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ \nвҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ вҖҢ\nRead in browser \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2026-04-27/gunman-s-motive-probed-after-dc-gala-attack>\n <https://www.bloomberg.com/>\n\n \n<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click?s=1148999&li=17868579&m=cee68ef49e1e07dda471dbc72a2057c6&p=04272026105321&lctg=d27c9f4c-3a6e-4424-83d8-08bd5867b1d0&stpe=default>\n \n<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click?s=1148999&li=17868579&m=cee68ef49e1e07dda471dbc72a2057c6&p=04272026105321&lctg=d27c9f4c-3a6e-4424-83d8-08bd5867b1d0&stpe=default>\nGood morning. The gunman in the DC gala attack is set to be arraigned today as \ninvestigators probe his motive. BritainвҖҷs king arrives in the US amid strained \nties. And we examine the $1 million retirement myth.Listen to the dayвҖҷs top \nstories <https://link.podtrac.com/gu6gyrzy>.\n\nвҖ” Marc Perrier\n\nMarket Snapshot\nS&P 500 Futures \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/ES1:IND?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n7,191.50-0.0%\nNasdaq 100 Futures \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/NQ1:IND?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n27,470.00+0.1%\nWTI crude oil futures \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/CL1:COM?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n$95.69+1.4%\nMarket data as of 06:50 AM ET. Data is subject to provider delays.Your \nwatchlist \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/markets/watchlist?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\nThe man accused of storming the White House CorrespondentsвҖҷ Dinner had spent \nyears quietlybuilding an arsenal \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/suspect-in-dc-dinner-attack-spent-several-years-acquiring-guns?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n, while preliminary evidence suggests that Cole Tomas Allen, who is expected to \nbe arraigned today, wastargeting \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2026-04-26/dc-gala-gunman-believed-to-be-targeting-us-officials-video?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n administration officials. The attack raisesfresh questions \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/another-attack-at-hinckley-hilton-raises-new-security-concerns?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n about security around President Donald Trump.\n\nOil gained as the Strait of Hormuz remained effectively impassable \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/latest-oil-market-news-and-analysis-for-april-27?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n and US-Iran talks stayed in limbo. IranвҖҷs foreign ministerarrived in Russia \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/iran-suggests-interim-deal-to-us-to-reopen-hormuz-axios-says?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n for a meeting with President Vladimir Putin, underscoring the diplomatic \nimpasse. Traders shrugged off an Axios report that Tehranmay be open \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/iran-offers-deal-to-us-to-reopen-strait-delay-nuclear-talks-axios-says?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n to an interim deal.\n\nKing Charles III arrives in Washington today for a four-day state visit \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/king-charles-us-visit-uk-monarch-tries-to-stop-another-split-with-america?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n, as tensions between the US and the UK remain strained. Trump has suggested \nthe British monarch could вҖңabsolutely \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-23/trump-tells-bbc-that-king-charles-s-visit-may-improve-us-uk-ties?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\nвҖқ help repair the relationship. Security around the trip will be underclose \nscrutiny \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2026-04-26/king-charles-security-under-review-ahead-of-dc-visit-video?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n following SaturdayвҖҷs shooting in Washington.\n\nWarsh Confirmation Set to Advance as GOP Holdout Backs Vote\nRead more \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/tillis-says-he-s-prepared-to-move-ahead-with-warsh-confirmation>\n\nBudget airlines seek a break. Carriers including Frontier and Avelo are asking \nthe White House for a$2.5 billion relief \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/budget-airlines-ask-white-house-for-2-5-billion-relief-plan?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n package in exchange for convertible equity stakes, the Wall Street Journal \nreported. The figure reflects how much more they expect to spend onjet fuel \nthis year \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-25/jet-fuel-s-mad-rise-and-trump-s-meddling-cloud-airline-outlook?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n than previously forecast.\n\nBrace for a wave of Big Tech earnings this week that could prove a \nmake-or-break moment \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/big-tech-s-16-trillion-earnings-week-is-make-or-break-for-rally?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n for the S&P 500вҖҷs record rally. Alphabet, Microsoft, Amazon, Meta, and Apple \nhave a combined value of nearly $16 trillion. Elsewhere, Elon Musk said X is \nclose to becoming an вҖңeverything app \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/musk-vies-to-turn-x-into-super-app-with-banking-tool-near-launch?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n,вҖқ with a new banking tool set to launch this month. And Meta is exploring ways \nto power AI data centers with solarenergy collected in space \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/meta-seeks-to-power-data-centers-with-energy-beamed-from-space?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n вҖ” far out.\n\nComing soon: Get the AI Today newsletter \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/ai-today>вҖ”chronicling the \ndisruptions and threats of AI on businesses, workers, governments and economies \nwith analysis from BloombergвҖҷs global newsroom.\n\n\n\n \n<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click?s=1099764&stpe=default&li=17868579&m=cee68ef49e1e07dda471dbc72a2057c6&p=04272026105321&lctg=d27c9f4c-3a6e-4424-83d8-08bd5867b1d0>\n\n \n<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click?s=1099764&stpe=default&li=17868579&m=cee68ef49e1e07dda471dbc72a2057c6&p=04272026105321&lctg=d27c9f4c-3a6e-4424-83d8-08bd5867b1d0>\nDeep Dive: Billionaire Backlash\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/how-google-s-sergey-brin-helped-fuel-a-political-war-in-california>\nSergey Brin and his partner Gerelyn Gilbert-Soto.Photographer: Neilson \nBarnard/Getty Images\nGoogle co-founder Sergey Brin has advanced a campaign against \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/how-google-s-sergey-brin-helped-fuel-a-political-war-in-california?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n a California proposal to tax billionaires, a measure that would affect his \nvast fortune.\n\n * Brin has left California, bought a home in Nevada \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-01-27/brin-linked-to-nevada-mansion-purchase-as-california-tax-looms?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n, and begun funding political efforts in the state, spending more than $58 \nmillion over the past four months.\n * Ultrawealthy donors, including Brin, have poured more than $270 million \ninto California politics as a heated battle unfolds over a proposal to levy a \n5% tax \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-01-08/california-wealth-tax-threat-pushes-billionaires-to-texas-florida?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n on billionairesвҖҷ wealth.  \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-26/how-google-s-sergey-brin-helped-fuel-a-political-war-in-california>\nThe Big Take\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2026-04-26/wall-street-s-quantum-computing-divide-goldman-retreats-jpmorgan-invests>\nScientists working on a neutral atom quantum computer at the National Quantum \nComputing Centre in Didcot.Photographer: Tom Skipp/Bloomberg\nGoldman Sachs retreated from quantum computing while JPMorgan has doubled \ndown, contrasting Wall StreetвҖҷs divide onharnessing the technology \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2026-04-26/wall-street-s-quantum-computing-divide-goldman-retreats-jpmorgan-invests?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n.\n\nBig Take Podcast\n\nApple Enters the AI Race With New CEO\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/audio/2026-04-24/big-take-apple-enters-the-ai-race-with-new-ceo-podcast>\nOpinion\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2026-04-27/does-fashion-s-return-to-the-1980s-predict-an-ai-bubble>\nThe Saint Laurent Womenswear Spring/Summer 2026 show in Paris.Photographer: \nStephane Cardinale/Corbis Entertainment\nFashion may be signaling economic trouble, Andrea Felsted writes. The return \nof the 1980s aestheticвҖ”defined by excess \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2026-04-27/does-fashion-s-return-to-the-1980s-predict-an-ai-bubble?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\nвҖ”echoes a period that preceded the 1987 stock market crash.\n\nMore Opinions\n\nAllison Schrager\n\nYale Is the Least of US Higher EducationвҖҷs Problems\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2026-04-26/yale-troubles-expose-a-deeper-problem-in-us-higher-education>\nNir Kaissar\n\nUS Stocks Will Keep Ignoring the Iran War\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2026-04-27/us-stocks-will-keep-ignoring-the-iran-war>\nPlay Alphadots!\n\nOur daily word puzzle with a plot twist.\n\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/games/alphadots?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/games/alphadots?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningapac>\nTodayвҖҷs clue is: Game of thrones?\n\nPlay now! \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/games/alphadots?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n\nBefore You Go\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/how-to-find-your-real-retirement-number>\nIllustration: Anna Haifisch\nAsk Americans how much they need to retire and one number comes up: $1 \nmillion. Better, simpler rules offer a more practical way to plan and lower the \nrisk of running out of money, no matter your target. HereвҖҷswhat to save \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/how-to-find-your-real-retirement-number?cmpid=042726_morningamer&utm_campaign=morningamer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_term=260427&utm_content=3872>\n instead.\n\nA Couple More\n\nHSBC Reviews $38,000-Per-Kid School Fee Perk for HK Bankers\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-27/hsbc-reviews-38-000-per-kid-school-fee-perk-for-hk-bankers>\nMadrid Locals Are Fighting to Preserve the CityвҖҷs Soul\n \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2026-04-27/madrid-s-new-luxury-amenities-are-threatening-the-city-s-laid-back-nightlife>\nMore From Bloomberg\n\nEnjoying Morning Briefing Americas? Get more news and analysis with our \nregional editions forAsia \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/morning-asia?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n andEurope \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/morning-europe?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n. Check out these newsletters, too:\n\n * Markets Daily \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/markets-daily?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n for whatвҖҷs moving in stocks, bonds, FX and commodities\n * Breaking News Alerts \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/breaking-news-alerts?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n for the biggest stories from around the world, delivered to your inbox as they \nhappen\n * Supply Lines \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/supply-lines?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n for daily insights into supply chains and global trade\n * FOIA Files \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/foia-files?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n for Jason LeopoldвҖҷs weekly newsletter uncovering government documents never \nseen before\nExplore all newsletters at Bloomberg.com \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/newsletters?utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&utm_campaign=morningamer>\n.\n\nWeвҖҷre improving your newsletter experience and weвҖҷd love your feedback. If \nsomething looks off, help us fine-tune your experience by reporting ithere \n<https://bmedia.iad1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_dhba7RmVMUuC9WC?bconnectId=E303D6C8D22F4D76B970EDBCD765D6CB>\n.\n\nFollow Us\n\n <https://www.instagram.com/bloombergbusiness/> <https://x.com/business> \n<https://www.linkedin.com/company/bloomberg-news/posts/> \n<https://bsky.app/profile/bloomberg.com> \n<https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Va2h58LDeONAZNBpcg09>\nYou received this message because you are subscribed to BloombergвҖҷs Morning \nBriefing Americas newsletter. If a friend forwarded you this message,sign up \nhere \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/morning-americas?source=NLshare> \nto get it in your inbox.\n\nUnsubscribe \n<https://www.bloomberg.com/account/newsletters/morning-americas?source=newsl